-- Coyotes Defeat Predators With 4-3 Overtime Win in NHL Semifinals
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-04-28T04:49:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/coyotes-defeat-predators-with-4-3-overtime-win-in-nhl-semifinals.html
Ray Whitney fired a 10-foot
backhand shot in overtime to give the Phoenix Coyotes a 4-3
victory over the  Nashville Predators  in the first game of their
Stanley Cup semifinal series.  The victory gives Phoenix the advantage over the Predators
in the best-of-seven National Hockey League series.  Radim Vrbata scored a power-play goal to give the Coyotes a
1-0 lead, before Brandon Yip tied the game at 1-1 in Jobing.com
Arena in Phoenix.  The Coyotes were ahead 3-2 at the end of the second period
on goals by Rostislav Klesla and Mikkel Boedker. Andrei Kostitsyn scored for the Predators.  Nashville’s Martin Erat tied the game with less than five
minutes left in regulation play, before Whitney got the winning
goal 14 minutes, four seconds into overtime.  In today’s games, the Washington Capitals visit the  New
York Rangers  and the St. Louis Blues host the  Los Angeles Kings 
in the first games of their second-round series.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
